
@startuml

' Define classes
class ResearchGroup {
  - id: int
  - name: string
  - department: string
  + getResearchers(): List<Researcher>
  + getWorkPackages(): List<WorkPackage>
}

class Researcher {
  - id: int
  - name: string
  - researchGroup: ResearchGroup
  + getWorkPackages(): List<WorkPackage>
}

class WorkPackage {
  - id: int
  - name: string
  - leaderResearchGroup: ResearchGroup
  + getResearchers(): List<Researcher>
}

' Define relationships
ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : belongsTo
ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : leads
Researcher "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : isAssignedTo

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **ResearchGroup** has a one-to-many relationship with **Researcher** (a group can have many researchers).
- **ResearchGroup** has a one-to-many relationship with **WorkPackage** (a group can lead multiple work packages).
- **Researcher** can be assigned to multiple **WorkPackages** (one-to-many).
- **WorkPackage** has a reference to its **leaderResearchGroup** (which is a ResearchGroup).

This model captures the requirement that:
- A researcher can be assigned to any WP, regardless of the leading RG.
- Service delivery between groups must be traceable via the assignments.
- When a researcher changes groups or a WP leadership changes, assignments are updated accordingly.

